  "text": "We previously showed that Rh factors are able to mediate ammonium transport in a bidirectional way [CITATION_1] . Their expression enhanced the ammonium excretion rate of triple-mepD cells growing on a medium supplied with arginine, a nitrogen source whose catabolism leads to intracellular ammonium production [CITATION_2] . In contrast to native HsRhAG or HsRhCG, expression of neosynthesized HsRhAG I61R , HsRhAG F65S or HsRhCG R202C allowed a reduced efficiency of ammonium excretion by triplemepD cells, indicating that the mutated proteins are altered in their ability to export ammonium ( Fig. 2e and 2f) . The HsRhAG and HsRhCG proteins were shown to confer to triple-mepD cells a resistance to high concentrations of methylammonium, a toxic analogue of ammonium, a phenotype possibly reflecting an increased efficiency in methylammonium excretion [CITATION_3] . In contrast to native HsRhAG and HsRhCG, the HsRhA-G I61R , HsRhAG F65S and HsRhCG R202C variants were unable to confer resistance to methylammonium to triple-mepD cells ( Fig. 2a  and 2b ).",
